-- Australia Reaches 238-4 on Fourth Day of Test; Clarke Is Out on Final Ball
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-12-06T07:33:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/australia-reaches-238-4-on-fourth-day-of-test-clarke-is-out-on-final-ball.html
Australia reached 238-4 in its second
innings at stumps on day four of the second Ashes cricket Test
against England in Adelaide.  Michael Clarke was out for 80 in the final ball of the day
to leave Mike Hussey unbeaten on 44.  England earlier declared at 620-5, a first-innings lead of
375 runs.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  